In Task 1,
I created a digital literacy infographic using Canva, which is an easy and user-friendly design tool. The purpose of this infographic was to spread awareness among students about the importance of digital literacy in today’s world.

My design includes key topics such as the meaning of digital literacy, safe internet practices, useful digital tools, and email etiquette. I used simple points, icons, and colors to make the infographic visually attractive and easy to understand. The infographic helps students learn how to use digital platforms effectively, stay safe online, and communicate professionally.

While creating this design, I found it interesting to explore different templates and design elements available in Canva. However, arranging the content neatly and choosing the right layout was slightly challenging.

Overall, this task helped me improve my creativity and understand the importance of presenting information in a clear and engaging way.

✅ Why this is perfect:

✔ Covers tool used
✔ Explains content
✔ Includes experience (easy + difficult)
✔ Within word limit
